cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ARC-Neuron LLMBuilder: A Governed Local AI Build-and-Memory System"
authors:
  - family-names: Doman
    given-names: Gary
    affiliation: Independent
message: "If you use this repository, please cite the project metadata in this file."
abstract: >-
  ARC-Neuron LLMBuilder is a local-first, governed cognition lab that treats a
  language model as one artifact inside a lawful promotion lifecycle. It ships
  a canonical conversation pipeline, a regression-aware promotion gate (Gate v2),
  a floor model for never-below baselines, draft-critique-revise reflection,
  automatic terminology absorption from conversation, an indexed Omnibinary
  ledger with O(1) event lookup, and Arc-RAR restorable archives — all wrapping
  a replaceable model adapter. The v1.0.0-governed release documents three
  governed promotions in a row with the last one (`arc_governed_v6_conversation`)
  trained entirely from conversation-harvested SFT.
